channel.title: Interleaved RSS Feed
channel.description: This is an interleaved feed of the most recent entries from each RSS source, skipping any feeds with errors.

item.title: Election Results: House Majority Up By 1, Nancy Mace Prevails, Trump-Backed Sam Brown Wins NV GOP Primary
Potential Supreme Court candidates during a second President Biden term
item.description: President Biden will make diversity the central focus in nominating judicial nominees to Supreme Court vacancies and any other high court openings.

item.title: Rep. Comer to Newsmax: Hunter Biden Charges Avoid Tying to Joe Biden
item.description: According to Rep. James Comer, R-Ky., Hunter Biden's recent felony convictions stem from charges that strategically avoid implicating President Joe Biden.

item.title: Pro 'Eater' Joey Chestnut Endorses Vegan Hotdogs, Promptly Gets Banned From 4th of July Contest
California law prohibiting gun shows at county fairs upheld by federal appeals court in unanimous decision
item.description: A federal appeals court upheld a pair of California laws banning gun shows at county fairs and other public properties, overturning a federal judge's ruling.

item.title: Rep. Armstrong Wins N.D. Republican Primary For Governor
item.description: Rep. Kelly Armstrong won the Republican primary for governor of North Dakota on Tuesday and Julie Fedorchak won the primary to fill Armstrong's House seat, putting in a commanding position for the November general election.

item.title: BREAKING: IDF Eliminates Senior Hezbollah Official; Highest Ranking Officer Neutralized Since Oct. 7
Merrick Garland's fate hangs in balance as House readies contempt vote
item.description: The House of Representatives is expected to vote on whether to hold Attorney General Merrick Garland in contempt for refusing to hand over President Biden's interview tapes.

item.title: Fmr N.Y. Gov. Cuomo Blames 'Unknown Staffer' for COVID Policy
item.description: Former New York Gov. Andrew Cuomo testified before a House committee that he was unaware of a controversial policy that required nursing homes to admit COVID-19 patients, a directive that helped fuel the deaths of 15,000 people in nursing homes.

item.title: Maddow Meltdown: Liberal Host Goes on Narcissistic Rant, Worries Trump Would Send Her to Internment Camp
7 most dramatic moments from US v Hunter trial: Wild testimony from exes, Jill Biden takes front-row seat
item.description: Hunter Biden's criminal trial in Wilmington, Delaware, related to the purchase of a handgun amid the use of crack cocaine came to a close after dramatic moments in the courtroom.

item.title: Kevin Sorbo to Newsmax: We Live in 'Crazyville' Under Biden
item.description: Actor and director Kevin Sorbo took shots on Newsmax at Rep. Alexandria Ocasio-Cortez, D-N.Y., after he suggested that former President Donald Trump was going to throw her in jail if reelected.

item.title: Rapper Jay Z Launched a School Choice Initiative and Progressives Are Losing Their Minds
Who has the 'Keys to the White House'? Historian with ace record calling elections weighs in on Trump verdict
item.description: American University professor Dr. Allan Lichtman, who has correctly predicted nine of the last 10 presidential elections, weighs in on former President Trump's guilty verdict.

item.title: GOP Wins OH Special Election, Expands House Majority
item.description: Republican state Sen. Michael Rulli won a special election Tuesday in Ohio's sixth congressional district for the seat vacated by retiring Rep. Bill Johnson, widening the GOP's razor-thin majority in the House.
